Divert specify: For plastic/polystyrene pieces 0-2,5 cm (OSPAR ID 117) and string and cords (OSPAR ID 32) the 100m beach was divided in a transect. The transect size counted was 5x30m, which accounted for about 7,5% of the area. The number counted was multiplied with a factor of 13,33. A 15 m long pile of seaweed washed up on the beach was full of pieces of marine litter. The largest pieces were counted. Then we took a 3 m long (20%) transects where all the small pieces were counted. The number counted was multiplied with a factor of 5 (100%)

Divert specify: Due to a misplacement of the beach markers only 91 meters of the beach was surveyed.

The counting of litter was divided into two parts, one part was 0-100 m and the second part was 100-135 m. Only the first part is submitted here. The results will be evaluated after 3 years.

Due to local wind and current conditions in the bay, litter accumulates differently on different parts of the beach.
Therefore, the 100 m stretch is divided into two sections:
- lots of litter: 63 meters (0 - 63 m)
- minor litter: 37 meters (63-100 m)
The counting is based on three replicas of 1 meter.
The entire stretch was first picked on large visible objects.
Then everything was counted in the three replicates.
The replicates were randomized within the respective sections:
- 2 replicas in the distance with the most litter (63 m)
- 1 replicate in the distance with less litter (37 meters)
The total amount of litter was calculated by multiplying the mean values of the replicates within each part distance with length of part. Then the quantities in the sub-sections were added to the quantities with large litter that was first picked along the entire stretch.

The distance was previously calculated is 135 meters. It is now divided into two sections:
STRENGTH 1: The actual 100 meter stretch that starts south of the bus cut and runs 100 meters north.
STRENGTH 2: A distance of 35 meters which should not be north of stretch 1.
The routes have been calculated separately and are reported in separate documents since 2016.
